# Page-Flip Flash Prevention

## Root cause
`react-pageflip` calls `updateFromHtml()` ‚Äî which **destroys and recreates ALL pages** ‚Äî every time its `children` prop reference changes. When `onFlip ‚Üí setCurrentSpread()` triggers a React re-render, the `spreads.flatMap(...)` produces a new children array, which triggers `updateFromHtml()` and causes a visible flash.

## THREE constraints that prevent the flash:

### 1. Memoize flipbook children ‚Äî depends ONLY on `spreads`
In `EditorCanvas.tsx`, the children passed to `<HTMLFlipBook>` MUST be memoized with only the `spreads` array as a dependency. **Do NOT include interaction state** (`currentSpreadIndex`, `selectedPhotoId`, `swapPhase`, etc.) in the dependency array or as props to `SpreadPage`.

```tsx
// ‚úÖ CORRECT ‚Äî stable reference, prevents updateFromHtml cascade
const flipPages = useMemo(() => spreads.flatMap((s, i) => [
  <SpreadPage key={`${s.id}-R`} spread={s} side="right" spreadIndex={i} />,
  <SpreadPage key={`${s.id}-L`} spread={s} side="left" spreadIndex={i} />,
]), [spreads])

// ‚ùå WRONG ‚Äî new array on every render, triggers page reinitialization
{spreads.flatMap((s, i) => [
  <SpreadPage key={...} isCurrent={i === currentSpreadIndex} selectedPhotoId={...} />,
])}
```

### 2. SpreadPage reads interaction state from the store
`SpreadPage` receives only `spread`, `side`, and `spreadIndex` as props. All interaction state (`isCurrent`, `selectedPhotoId`, `selectPhoto`, `swapPhase`, etc.) is read via `useEditorStore()` subscriptions inside the component.

### 3. SpreadPage inner wrapper structure
The outer ref div (`ref={ref}`) MUST remain bare (no inline styles). All visual styles MUST live on the inner wrapper div. `react-pageflip` overwrites the ref's `style.cssText` every frame.

```tsx
// ‚úÖ CORRECT
<div ref={ref} data-density="hard">
  <div style={{ backgroundColor, overflow: 'hidden', transform: 'scaleX(-1)' }}>
    {/* content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Defense-in-depth CSS
In `src/index.css`, keep `transform-style: flat !important` on `.stf__item` to prevent 3D bleed-through:
```css
.album-flipbook .stf__item {
  transform-style: flat !important;
}
```

### DO NOT
- Add `backfaceVisibility: hidden` to the inner wrapper (causes GPU artifacts with `scaleX(-1)`)
- Pass interaction state as props to SpreadPage (breaks children memoization)
- Include `currentSpreadIndex` in the flipPages useMemo deps
